sec.p:
As illustrated in Fig. 3, from the R and Q peaks in the ECG and the AO, AC, MO and MC fiducial points in the SCG waveform we may estimate the RR interval, RRI (i.e. the time interval between consecutive R peaks) and the Cardiac Time Intervals, CTIs, considered as indexes of cardiac mechanical function and defined as follows:
Pre Ejection Period (PEP) = the time delay from the Q wave in the ECG to the AO fiducial point in the SCG;
Isovolumic Contraction Time (ICT) = the time delay from MC to AO;
Left Ventricular Ejection Time (LVET) = the time delay from AO to AC;
Isovolumic Relaxation Time (IRT) = the time delay from AC to MO.

In case at least one of the 20 beats preceding the current beat contained a valid IRP, the IRPRdelay of the valid beat closest to the current beat was taken as reference, IRPRdelay
